title: Commission Regulation (EEC) No 966/84 of 9 April 1984 re-establishing the levying of customs duties on other footwear, falling within subheading 64.02 B and originating in the Philippines, to which the preferential tariff arrangements set out in Council Regulation (EEC) No 3569/83 apply
header:
COMMISSION  REGULATION (EEC) No 966/84
of 9 April 1984
re-establishing the levying of customs duties on other footwear, falling within subheading 64.02 B and originating in the Philippines, to which the preferential tariff arrangements set out in Council Regulation (EEC) No 3569/83 apply
THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN
COMMUNITIES
main_body:
As from 13 April 1984, the levying of customs duties, suspended pursuant to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3569/83, shall be re-established on imports into the Community of the following products originating in the Philippines:
1.2 //   //   // CCT heading No  // Description  //   //  // 64.02 (NIMEXE codes 64.02-60, 61, 69, 99)  // Footwear with outer soles of leather or composition leather, footwear (other than footwear falling within heading No 64.01) with outer soles of rubber or artificial plastic material:  //   // B. Other  //   //

This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities.
This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States.
attachments:
Done at Brussels, 9 April 1984.
For the Commission
Karl-Heinz NARJES
Member of the Commission
(1) OJ No L 362, 24. 12. 1983, p. 1.
